<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idabc82f18-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5" identifier="/us/usc/t10/s20002"><num value="20002">§ 20002.</num><heading> Members: duty status</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Under regulations prescribed by the Secretary of the Air Force, each member of the Space Force shall be placed in one of the following duty statuses:</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idabc82f19-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5" identifier="/us/usc/t10/s20002/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> Space Force active status.</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idabc82f1a-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5" identifier="/us/usc/t10/s20002/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> Space Force inactive status.</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idabc82f1b-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5" identifier="/us/usc/t10/s20002/3"><num value="3">(3)</num><content> Space Force retired status.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="idabc82f1c-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/118/31/dA/tXVII/s1714">Pub. L. 118–31, div. A, title XVII, § 1714</ref>, <date date="2023-12-22">Dec. 22, 2023</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/137/626">137 Stat. 626</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
